as this year comes to an end , i can say it was the biggest rollercoaster of my life . i have been so lucky and blessed to do what i do every day . and to work with such amazing people . this year has taught me so much , in moments where i was thrown into a rink and didn’t  know how to fight but somehow still won many battles even the ones where i felt like i couldn’t get up from . this year taught me to take care of my health ,love every last minute with those you love and always tell them you love them when you have the chance . i made the most beautiful music and so many new friends  and loved love again . i made some of the greatest memories and was able to do it all with the people i cherish most . thank you for each and everyone of you for making the impact not only in my life but in your own and everyone else’s as well . thank you for being patient and for loving and support me through this journey and for the countless messages in moments were you were worried . your love and appreciation doesn’t go unnoticed . and i hope with this new year brings you so much happiness and joyful moments that it brings you the most tip top health and hands you the most love in the world because you deserve it even when you think you don’t . i can’t wait to share new music and memories and scream and cry and enjoy every beautiful moment with you all . heres to a beautiful year and making it count . thank you for 2022 ( but you can leave now ) can’t wait to kick 2023s  assss . love y’all , happy new year . 
-fia

Happy #BellLetsTalk Day! Learn more about actions you can take to support your mental health and the mental health of others: bell.ca/letstalk
 
as some of you may or may not know i have suffered from anxiety and panic disorder since i was 12 since then it has grown into depression and ocd and since then  i will always try to do my best to use my platform to spread the importance of mental health . i know it’s not easy to talk about and you might feel trapped and alone . i promise you that you are so loved and you so strong more than you think. there have been times my anxiety has stopped me from doing many things just because it feels the need to ruin my day  and i’ve honestly sometimes allowed it to because i was so afraid . you are always welcome to message me and to talk . and please always spread kindness because you truly never know what some people are going through . use the link above for more info to help yourself or those you care about . you are so loved and so special and you are more than enough you are definitely worthy and strong . never forget that . ❤️ #bellletstalk

Markus, 

Since the very first day I met you , you changed my life and I wouldn’t change it for the world . You’ve given me every reason to smile and be the happiest girl that’s walked these streets . Showed me that I was capable of anything In this world and never thought I was to crazy for having the dreams I did. You inspired me and millions of other people in this world everyday . You were an angel from the second we met .We would laugh about how one day we would rule the world and move to Los Angeles and have a mansion full of YouTubers cause we would take over the internet . We would talk about our deepest secrets and our fears that would consume us . We would laugh till our tummy’s would hurt and FaceTime eachother when the world got a little to quiet for our liking . I remember the very first day I met you . god made me the luckiest girl that day . He gave me one of the biggest blessings in my life, you . You never forgot to tell me I was perfect in every-way and how the world was lucky to have me but if only the world knew how lucky they were to have known you. We would talk like time never existed like no matter how many hours we would pass it always felt to short when it came time to hang up the phone . Wherever you are I hope you are at peace . I hope you know every part of you lives in and with me everyday . I wish  we knew forever at the time would be cut short maybe we would have done things a lot differently but you taught me so much with the so little time we had and never let a second go by without a smile on your face because as much as this world is a very dark place sometimes, you were such a light in it so thank you for changing my life and loving me the way you did . You took a big part of me and I’m forever grateful I got to know your heart. You are perfect my love … I hope you’re resting in peace and carrying that beautiful smile with you everywhere you go . 
I miss your laugh it was my favourite thing about you . 
Forever and ever 

🧡sof
